[
    {
        "content": "<p>I see CapabilityStatement.rest.resource.searchRevInclude now in the CapabilityStatement, but I am not clear on how to use it. My use-case is to indicate that my server does support reverse include for Provenance resources. That is to say that all queries of all the resources I support can have a reverse include for Provenance of the results... what would this look like in a capability statement?</p>",
        "id": 169732925,
        "sender_full_name": "John Moehrke",
        "timestamp": 1562357217
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>For example :</p>",
        "id": 169877974,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Haas",
        "timestamp": 1562598871
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>GET [base]/MedicationRequest?_revinclude=Provenance:target</code></p>",
        "id": 169877991,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Haas",
        "timestamp": 1562598890
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>in the CS would have</p>",
        "id": 169878321,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Haas",
        "timestamp": 1562599112
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span>     ],\n          &quot;referencePolicy&quot; : [\n            &quot;resolves&quot;\n          ],\n          &quot;searchInclude&quot; : [\n            &quot;MedicationRequest:medication&quot;\n          ],\n          ,\n          &quot;searchRevInclude&quot; : [\n            &quot;Provenance:target&quot;\n          ],\n</pre></div>",
        "id": 169878326,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Haas",
        "timestamp": 1562599116
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>this would be in every <code>CapabilityStatement.rest.resource</code></p>",
        "id": 169878518,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Haas",
        "timestamp": 1562599270
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Excellent. thanks. I will try that.</p>",
        "id": 169880276,
        "sender_full_name": "John Moehrke",
        "timestamp": 1562600614
    }
]